:R-HSA-418555  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The general function of the G alpha (s) subunit (Gs) is to activate adenylate cyclase (Tesmer et al. 1997), which in turn produces cAMP, leading to the activation of cAMP-dependent protein kinases (often referred to collectively as Protein Kinase A). The signal from the ligand-stimulated GPCR is amplified because the receptor can activate several Gs heterotrimers before it is inactivated. Another downstream effector of G alpha (s) is the protein tyrosine kinase c-Src (Ma et al. 2000)." ;
        rdfs:label          "G alpha (s) signalling events" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Jupe, S, 2009-09-09" , "Reviewed: Akkerman, JW, 2009-06-03" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Jupe, S, 2009-04-23 16:22:25" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-418555" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-388396/R-HSA-388396> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

